  "prompt": "What are the legal precedents related to money laundering cases?",
  "response": "There have been several significant legal precedents in money laundering cases, including key Supreme Court decisions and landmark prosecutions. Some notable cases involve:\n\n1. United States v. Santos (2008)\n- Supreme Court addressed money laundering statute interpretation\n- Clarified definition of \"proceeds\" in financial transactions\n\n2. Bank of Credit and Commerce International (BCCI) case\n- Major international money laundering investigation\n- Resulted in significant financial institution reforms\n\n3. Racketeering Influenced and Corrupt Organizations (RICO) Act cases\n- Provided legal framework for prosecuting complex financial crimes\n- Allowed seizure of assets connected to illegal activities\n\n4. Basel Committee recommendations\n- Established international anti-money laundering standards\n- Influenced global legal approaches to financial crime prevention\n\n5. Bank Secrecy Act enforcement actions\n- Created reporting requirements for financial institutions\n- Established legal mechanisms for detecting suspicious transactions\n\nThese are general legal precedents. For specific detailed analysis, I recommend consulting legal professionals or comprehensive legal research resources.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these specific cases or legal principles?",
